sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Application
    participant SP as SyncProducer
    participant B as MessageBroker
    participant Sub as Subscription
    participant H as Handler
    participant WR as WithRetry
    participant DLH as DeadLetterHandler

    Note over App,DLH: Message Production Flow

    App->>SP: SendValue(ctx, "orders", orderData)
    SP->>SP: Serialize (JSONSerializer)
    SP->>SP: Compress (GzipCompressor)
    SP->>SP: Set content-type header
    SP->>SP: Set content-encoding header
    SP->>B: Publish(ctx, "orders", msg)
    B-->>SP: nil (success)
    SP->>SP: Increment SentCount
    SP-->>App: nil

    Note over App,DLH: Message Consumption Flow

    App->>B: Subscribe(ctx, "orders", wrappedHandler)
    B-->>App: Subscription

    B->>WR: handler(ctx, msg)
    WR->>H: handler(ctx, msg)
    H-->>WR: error (transient failure)

    WR->>WR: Check IsRetryableError
    WR->>WR: Calculate Delay (attempt 1)
    WR->>WR: Sleep BackoffBase * Multiplier^1

    WR->>H: handler(ctx, msg) [retry 1]
    H-->>WR: error (still failing)

    WR->>WR: Calculate Delay (attempt 2)
    WR->>WR: Sleep BackoffBase * Multiplier^2

    WR->>H: handler(ctx, msg) [retry 2]
    H-->>WR: error (max retries reached)
    WR-->>B: error (last error)

    Note over App,DLH: Dead Letter Queue Flow

    App->>DLH: Handle(ctx, msg, originalErr)
    DLH->>DLH: Clone message
    DLH->>DLH: Set x-dlq-reason header
    DLH->>DLH: Set x-dlq-original-topic header
    DLH->>DLH: Set x-dlq-timestamp header
    DLH->>B: Publish(ctx, "orders.dlq", dlqMsg)
    B-->>DLH: nil
    DLH->>DLH: Increment Count
    DLH->>DLH: Invoke OnFailure callback
    DLH-->>App: nil

    Note over App,DLH: Async Production Flow

    App->>App: ap := NewAsyncProducer(broker, 5000)
    App->>App: ap.Start(ctx)
    App->>App: ap.Send("logs", msg)
    Note right of App: Non-blocking: queued<br/>in buffered channel

    activate B
    Note right of B: Background goroutine<br/>pulls from channel
    B->>B: Publish(ctx, "logs", msg)
    deactivate B

    Note over App,DLH: Batch Consumption Flow

    App->>App: bc := NewBatchConsumer(50, 2s, batchHandler)
    App->>App: bc.Start(ctx)
    B->>App: bc.AsHandler()(ctx, msg1)
    App->>App: Add to buffer
    B->>App: bc.AsHandler()(ctx, msg2)
    App->>App: Add to buffer
    Note right of App: Timer fires or<br/>buffer reaches 50
    App->>App: Flush(ctx)
    App->>App: batchHandler(ctx, [msg1, msg2, ...])
